The paper discusses school choice mechanisms and their impact on student welfare, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of simulations and computational experiments also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper's emphasis on decision-making and optimization could also place it in the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
